  "text": "It is important to note that in step 1, the external information of group labels is utilized to calculate the CLfdr; this is the feature from a separate analysis. However, in steps 2 and 3, the group labels are dropped and the rankings of all hypotheses are determined globally; this is the feature from a pooled analysis. [CITATION_1] showed that the CLfdr procedure is asymptotically valid and optimal. Unlike for the separate analysis, the group-wise FDR levels of the CLfdr procedure, which are in general different from α, are adaptively weighted among groups.",
